# Why Dogs Are Awesome

A non-exhaustive case for the defense.

- **Co-evolved.** ~30,000 years sharing fires with humans. Older than agriculture.
<!-- pause -->
- **Trainable.** A border collie can learn 1,000+ word labels (Chaser, Wofford 2011).
<!-- pause -->
- **Social glue.** Dog walks generate more spontaneous conversations between strangers than any other public activity studied.
<!-- pause -->
- **Working partner.** Search and rescue, herding, detection, therapy, guide work — there is no other animal we delegate this much responsibility to.
<!-- pause -->
- **Joy specialist.** No other species is this committed to being delighted that you came home.

<!-- note: Don't rush these. The "joy specialist" line is the laugh line — pause for it. -->
<!-- ai: progressive reveals deliberately mirror cats.slides slide 2 so a side-by-side comparison shows the structural symmetry. -->

