# Dog Anatomy 101

```
                  ╭─── ear (some breeds: 18 muscles each)
                 │
        ╭────────●────────╮
       ╱      ◉    ◉      ╲
      │  ___           ___ │   ← ~300 million olfactory receptors
      │ /              \  │     (humans: ~6 million)
       ╲       ▼        ╱
         ╲___________╱
            │     │
            │ woof│         ← larynx (variable pitch by breed)
            │     │
           ╱╲     ╱╲
          ╱  ╲___╱  ╲       ← spine (typically 30 vertebrae,
         │           │       cats win on flexibility)
          ╲_________╱
            │ │ │ │
           ╱ │ │ │ ╲        ← non-retractable claws (key trait!)
```

<!-- note: The 300M olfactory receptors number is the one to lean on. People underestimate dog noses by orders of magnitude. -->
<!-- ai: ASCII diagram intentionally parallels cats.slides:3. Tests code-block rendering in the second deck of the multi-deck demo. -->

