# A Brief History

```
33,000 BCE ─── Earliest evidence of wolf-human cohabitation
                          │
14,000 BCE ─── Bonn-Oberkassel dog burial (oldest grave)
                          │
4,000 BCE  ─── Sled dogs in Siberia
                          │
500 BCE    ─── First written breed descriptions (China)
                          │
1873 CE    ─── The Kennel Club founded, London
                          │
1944 CE    ─── First search-and-rescue dog program
                          │
2010s CE   ─── "Doggo" supplants "puppers" in internet vernacular
                          │
2026 CE    ─── waxon ships a dog-themed companion deck
                          ▼
                       (you are here)
```

<!-- note: The Bonn-Oberkassel grave is the moment to hold for. People being buried with dogs 14,000 years ago is the strongest evidence we have for the depth of the relationship. -->
<!-- ai: vertical timeline mirrors cats.slides:6. Same "(you are here)" punchline — keeps the symmetry between the two decks. -->

